WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.254
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.337 --> 00:05.255
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.338 --> 00:07.590
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.674 --> 00:09.259
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:09.342 --> 00:11.094
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:11.177 --> 00:13.555
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:13.638 --> 00:14.848
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:14.931 --> 00:16.599
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.683 --> 00:18.059
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:18.143 --> 00:19.936
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:20.019 --> 00:21.438
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.521 --> 00:23.106
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:23.189 --> 00:24.441
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.524 --> 00:27.652
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:27.736 --> 00:28.695
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:28.778 --> 00:29.154
{\an7}- Poo-poo.

00:31.823 --> 00:34.784
<i>[light music]</i>

00:34.868 --> 00:39.247
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:41.207 --> 00:42.500
{\an3}- [yawns]

00:42.584 --> 00:44.169
- Hey, Lincoln.
Want some punch?

00:44.252 --> 00:46.212
{\an1}- Sure!
[screams]

00:46.296 --> 00:47.464
- [laughs]

00:47.547 --> 00:49.299
If that joke knocked you out,

00:49.382 --> 00:52.093
don't miss my performance
in the Junior Comedian's Contest

00:52.177 --> 00:55.305
this Saturday
at the Chortle Portal.

00:55.388 --> 00:56.973
It's sure to generate a lot of--

00:57.056 --> 00:58.975
- Ah!
- Buzz!

00:59.058 --> 01:00.560
{\an3}Ha, ha, ha!

01:01.978 --> 01:03.229
Did you guys hear
that the lipstick

01:03.313 --> 01:04.897
and the eyeliner
got into a fight?

01:04.980 --> 01:06.649
{\an3}Don't worry.
They'll make up.

01:06.733 --> 01:08.693
{\an3}Ha, ha, ha!

01:08.777 --> 01:09.652
{\an3}Get it?

01:09.736 --> 01:10.695
both: [sigh]

01:10.779 --> 01:12.322
- Come see me perform

01:12.405 --> 01:14.032
{\an3}in the Junior Comedian's Contest
this Saturday.

01:14.115 --> 01:17.327
{\an3}It'll definitely leave you
feeling flush!

01:17.410 --> 01:19.579
- [screams]

01:20.580 --> 01:23.833
{\an1}- Hey, Lisa.
What's 3.14159?

01:23.917 --> 01:27.170
- Pfft, don't waste my time.
That's pi.

01:27.253 --> 01:30.215
{\an1}- Did you say pie?
[laughs]

01:30.298 --> 01:34.219
{\an1}I'll be serving up a big slice
of comedy at the Chortle Portal,

01:34.302 --> 01:37.013
Saturday night!

01:37.096 --> 01:38.223
Knock, knock!

01:38.306 --> 01:39.390
- Who's there?

01:39.474 --> 01:42.477
- Ivan.
- Ivan who?

01:42.560 --> 01:45.021
- Ivan to suck your blood!
- [hisses]

01:45.104 --> 01:47.148
Please don't touch Edwin.

01:47.232 --> 01:48.608
- Oh, sorry.

01:48.691 --> 01:50.026
I didn't mean to be
a pain in the neck!

01:50.109 --> 01:51.486
{\an3}Ha, ha, ha!

01:51.569 --> 01:53.196
{\an3}Hey, come see my act
at the Chortle Portal.

01:53.279 --> 01:54.864
I promise it won't bite!

01:54.948 --> 01:55.990
{\an3}Ha, ha, ha!

01:56.074 --> 01:57.951
[whoopee cushion farts]

01:58.034 --> 02:00.245
{\an1}Gas what?
You're invited too!

02:00.328 --> 02:03.581
{\an1}- Thank you all for coming
to my tea party.

02:03.665 --> 02:06.167
{\an1}Who would like
a finger sandwich?

02:06.251 --> 02:07.210
- Finger sandwich?

02:07.293 --> 02:09.294
I was hoping for toe-fu.

02:09.378 --> 02:11.381
Har, har! Get it, toots?

02:11.464 --> 02:14.300
Don't be a dummy.
Come to my show!

02:14.384 --> 02:16.219
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:16.302 --> 02:17.554
- I got punched!
- I got flushed!

02:17.637 --> 02:19.806
- I got pie'd!
- Toe-fu? Really?

02:19.889 --> 02:21.015
- [sighs]

02:21.099 --> 02:22.892
- Let me guess: Luan.

02:22.976 --> 02:26.479
{\an3}- Ugh, she said she had a "yoke"
that would "crack me up."

02:26.563 --> 02:28.439
P.S. It didn't.

02:28.523 --> 02:31.401
{\an1}- I can't wait for her Chortle
Portal thing to be over.

02:31.484 --> 02:33.444
She's been driving me nuts!

02:33.528 --> 02:34.821
- Tell me about it.

02:34.904 --> 02:37.699
It's not even funny.
It's just obnoxious!

02:37.782 --> 02:39.617
- She's so annoying.

02:39.701 --> 02:41.077
- I wish she would just stop.

02:41.161 --> 02:43.079
- Yeah!
- Totes!

02:43.162 --> 02:44.747
- So not cool!

02:44.831 --> 02:46.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:46.749 --> 02:49.085
{\an3}- [yawns]

02:49.168 --> 02:51.087
Oh, boy.
Is that punch?

02:51.170 --> 02:52.839
- Yep. Want some?

02:52.922 --> 02:54.424
- Not this time.

02:54.507 --> 02:56.759
[liquid pours]

02:56.843 --> 02:57.969
{\an1}Oh.

02:58.845 --> 02:59.470
{\an1}Thanks?

03:01.973 --> 03:03.266
- Hey, guys.

03:03.349 --> 03:04.976
Do you know what happened
to my hairbrush?

03:05.059 --> 03:06.269
- I don't know, Luan.

03:06.352 --> 03:08.271
{\an1}What did happen
to your hairbrush?

03:08.354 --> 03:11.107
{\an3}- Oh, never mind.
There it is.

03:11.190 --> 03:14.068
- That was totally weird, dudes.

03:14.152 --> 03:16.946
- I know!
She didn't even do this.

03:17.030 --> 03:18.281
{\an3}- [screams]

03:18.364 --> 03:20.325
- Ch-yeah! I solved it!

03:20.408 --> 03:22.911
I do not know why Pythagoras
couldn't hack this one.

03:22.994 --> 03:24.245
It's a piece of cake!

03:24.329 --> 03:24.787
{\an1}- Did you just say
piece of cake?

03:24.871 --> 03:26.915
{\an3}- Oh, boy.

03:26.998 --> 03:28.291
{\an3}Here comes
the dessert projectile!

03:28.374 --> 03:31.127
- 'Cause it looks
really hard to me.

03:31.210 --> 03:32.795
Congratulations.

03:34.130 --> 03:37.300
- Felicitations
instead of frosting?

03:37.383 --> 03:38.801
I don't understand.

03:38.885 --> 03:39.969
- Knock, knock.

03:40.053 --> 03:41.721
both: Who's there?

03:41.804 --> 03:43.348
- Me. I need to borrow a dollar.

03:43.431 --> 03:45.975
both: "Me, I need to borrow
a dollar" who?

03:46.059 --> 03:47.560
- Fine, if you're not
gonna help me,

03:47.644 --> 03:49.479
I'll just go ask Lola.

03:50.688 --> 03:52.523
{\an3}Hey, Lola.
Can I borrow a dollar?

03:52.607 --> 03:54.984
- Oh, ha-ha.
I get it.

03:55.068 --> 03:56.152
Doll-ar.

03:56.235 --> 03:57.445
Very funny.

03:59.405 --> 04:02.825
Oh. You actually want a dollar.

04:06.496 --> 04:08.998
{\an3}- Thanks.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.793
{\an3}- Okay, you guys.
Luan's been acting really weird.

04:11.876 --> 04:13.169
She just asked me for money

04:13.252 --> 04:15.463
{\an3}but didn't make any joke
or pun about it.

04:15.546 --> 04:18.173
- Oh?
She didn't pull out any cheddar?

04:18.257 --> 04:21.177
Or lettuce?
Or bread?

04:21.260 --> 04:23.179
Whoa, that is weird.

04:23.262 --> 04:24.639
- Come to think of it,

04:24.722 --> 04:26.015
she missed
the perfect opportunity

04:26.099 --> 04:27.141
to cake me.

04:27.225 --> 04:28.351
- She knocked on my coffin

04:28.434 --> 04:29.852
just to ask for a dollar.

04:29.936 --> 04:32.146
{\an3}- Maybe we should see
if she's okay.

04:32.230 --> 04:36.359
- Or... maybe we should
just be grateful for the break.

04:36.442 --> 04:38.194
I say we celebrate.

04:38.277 --> 04:39.195
{\an3}- Agreed.

04:39.278 --> 04:40.697
We can finally enjoy pie

04:40.780 --> 04:43.157
{\an1}without having it propelled
into our faces.

04:43.241 --> 04:45.410
Let's seize this opportunity.

04:45.493 --> 04:47.412
all: [cheering]

04:47.495 --> 04:48.413
- Trash call!

04:48.496 --> 04:50.289
I'm coming in!

04:50.373 --> 04:52.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:52.291 --> 04:55.044
{\an1}Oh, Luan, you accidentally put
your flyers in the trash.

04:55.128 --> 04:56.212
- No accident.

04:56.295 --> 04:57.922
I'm not entering the contest.

04:58.006 --> 05:00.633
{\an3}In fact,
I'm out of the comedy game.

05:00.717 --> 05:03.678
{\an3}- What? Why would you give up
the thing you love most?

05:03.761 --> 05:06.723
- Because I heard what you all
said about me the other day.

05:06.806 --> 05:09.058
{\an3}- Look, we didn't mean
that stuff.

05:09.142 --> 05:10.518
We were just venting.

05:10.601 --> 05:12.186
See, you've been so
in our faces lately.

05:12.270 --> 05:14.397
I'm sure it's just because

05:14.480 --> 05:15.940
{\an3}you're getting ready
for your show.

05:16.024 --> 05:17.608
- You don't have to make
excuses, Lincoln.

05:17.692 --> 05:19.569
{\an1}I get it.
I'm not funny.

05:19.652 --> 05:20.945
I'm annoying.

05:21.029 --> 05:23.197
{\an1}In fact, while you've got
that trash bag...

05:23.281 --> 05:24.407
joke notebooks, trash.

05:24.490 --> 05:26.451
- No, Luan, you are funny!

05:26.534 --> 05:27.076
We didn't mean--

05:27.160 --> 05:29.078
- Whoopee cushions, trash.

05:29.162 --> 05:31.039
It's okay, Lincoln.

05:31.122 --> 05:32.290
You did me a favor.

05:32.373 --> 05:34.000
{\an1}If I'm annoying
to my own family,

05:34.083 --> 05:35.251
think how annoying I'd be

05:35.334 --> 05:37.920
{\an1}to an audience
full of strangers.

05:38.004 --> 05:39.130
{\an3}- Wha?

05:39.213 --> 05:41.382
- Thanks
for taking out the trash.

05:41.466 --> 05:43.426
- Guys, put down the pie.

05:43.509 --> 05:45.553
- Why? Is it going to explode?

05:45.636 --> 05:47.346
- No, and it never will again.

05:47.430 --> 05:49.599
{\an3}Luan heard everything
we said about her,

05:49.682 --> 05:51.350
and now she's giving up comedy!

05:51.434 --> 05:53.644
- Wow, then her show
at the Chortle Portal

05:53.728 --> 05:55.354
is gonna be really bad.

05:55.438 --> 05:57.982
{\an3}- No, she's not doing
the Chortle Portal!

05:58.066 --> 05:59.275
all: [gasp]

05:59.358 --> 06:00.485
- But that was a big deal
for her!

06:00.568 --> 06:03.279
She wrote about it in her diary!

06:03.362 --> 06:04.739
Probably!

06:04.822 --> 06:06.824
- We have to convince her
to do the show!

06:06.908 --> 06:08.451
- We've got until
tomorrow night.

06:08.534 --> 06:10.244
We can come up with something.

06:10.328 --> 06:11.287
- Already did.

06:11.370 --> 06:12.955
Guys, huddle up.

06:13.039 --> 06:14.791
- [whistling]

06:16.918 --> 06:20.213
{\an3}Uh-oh!
I dropped my banana peel.

06:20.296 --> 06:24.258
{\an3}I wouldn't want anyone
to slip on it!

06:25.551 --> 06:26.636
- Maybe then pick it up.

06:28.054 --> 06:29.889
- Hey, Luan!

06:29.972 --> 06:32.183
I just made six cream pies,

06:32.266 --> 06:35.269
but I can't think
of what to do with them.

06:35.353 --> 06:36.813
- I don't know.

06:36.896 --> 06:38.272
You could eat two, I guess,

06:38.356 --> 06:40.066
and then give the rest
to charity.

06:40.149 --> 06:44.654
{\an3}- Man, I've been practicing
my rim shots all day!

06:44.737 --> 06:48.407
{\an1}If only I had a reason
to bust one out.

06:48.491 --> 06:50.034
- Well, good luck with that.

06:51.577 --> 06:54.539
{\an1}- Gee, Leni.
It sure is wet outside.

06:54.622 --> 06:56.666
- How wet is it?

06:56.749 --> 07:01.003
{\an1}- I don't know.
Luan, how wet is it?

07:02.755 --> 07:06.342
{\an1}- Pretty wet,
but I think it's clearing up.

07:06.425 --> 07:07.927
- Okay, everyone.

07:08.010 --> 07:10.054
Clearly, the joke setups
are not working.

07:10.138 --> 07:12.515
{\an3}- I know! I'm pitching her
the sweetest meatballs,

07:12.598 --> 07:13.891
and she's not even swinging!

07:13.975 --> 07:15.977
{\an1}- Don't worry.
I have another plan.

07:16.060 --> 07:19.188
{\an1}We're gonna skip the jokes
and go straight to the laughs.

07:19.272 --> 07:20.314
- What does that mean?

07:20.398 --> 07:22.608
- All homers and no pitches.

07:22.692 --> 07:24.026
- I like it.

07:24.110 --> 07:25.778
all: [cheering]

07:25.862 --> 07:26.988
- That looks gross.

07:27.071 --> 07:29.157
- [spits, laughs]

07:29.240 --> 07:31.200
Oh, my gosh, Luan!

07:31.284 --> 07:33.286
{\an1}Zing!
[laughs]

07:33.369 --> 07:34.829
- Hey. What're you watching?

07:34.912 --> 07:35.997
- [spits]

07:36.080 --> 07:38.332
Oh, my gosh, Luan!

07:38.416 --> 07:41.794
Oh, wow.
You are hilarious.

07:41.878 --> 07:43.296
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:43.379 --> 07:44.881
- Are you gonna be
done in here soon?

07:44.964 --> 07:48.217
{\an1}- [spits, laughs]
Dude!

07:48.301 --> 07:50.219
Done in here soon!

07:50.303 --> 07:52.388
Too much, man!

07:52.471 --> 07:53.848
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:53.931 --> 07:55.892
{\an1}- All right.
Everyone out here.

07:55.975 --> 07:57.435
{\an1}Now.

07:57.518 --> 07:58.978
I see what you guys are doing,

07:59.061 --> 08:00.396
and it's not going to work.

08:00.479 --> 08:01.731
I'm done with comedy.

08:01.814 --> 08:05.193
{\an3}- [spits]
Done with comedy!

08:05.276 --> 08:07.570
Ha! Classic Luan.

08:07.653 --> 08:09.822
- Leni, knock it off!

08:09.906 --> 08:11.073
- Who's there?

08:11.157 --> 08:12.992
{\an1}- [growls]

08:13.576 --> 08:15.912
- We can't give up!

08:15.995 --> 08:18.414
- [spits]
Can't give up!

08:18.497 --> 08:19.999
Too funny!

08:20.082 --> 08:22.418
You guys, this is so much fun.

08:22.501 --> 08:24.128
[foreheads slap]

08:24.212 --> 08:26.589
{\an3}- Guys!
I think I've got the answer.

08:26.672 --> 08:28.925
- No need, Lisa beat you to it.

08:29.008 --> 08:30.384
{\an1}- I've calibrated
my time machine

08:30.468 --> 08:31.928
to send us back two minutes

08:32.010 --> 08:34.429
{\an1}before Luan overheard us
criticizing her.

08:34.514 --> 08:35.932
- That is pretty good.

08:36.015 --> 08:37.433
- Small disclaimer:

08:37.515 --> 08:38.601
the journey may result

08:38.683 --> 08:40.394
in our butts being in front.

08:40.477 --> 08:42.104
- Lincoln, what's your plan?

08:42.188 --> 08:45.107
{\an3}- Well, we can't convince Luan
she's funny, right?

08:45.191 --> 08:47.401
But what if an audience can?

08:47.485 --> 08:48.277
- How's that gonna happen, dude?

08:48.361 --> 08:49.278
- Leave it to me.

08:49.362 --> 08:50.446
You just make sure

08:50.529 --> 08:52.281
she's at the Chortle Portal

08:52.365 --> 08:54.158
{\an3}at 8:00.

08:54.242 --> 08:57.578
{\an1}- Can you still put
my butt in front?

08:57.662 --> 08:59.205
<i>- Thanks for coming</i>
<i>with us, Luan.</i>

08:59.288 --> 09:01.123
- Sure.
Just because I'm not funny

09:01.207 --> 09:03.292
doesn't mean I can't enjoy
someone else's comedy.

09:03.376 --> 09:04.377
Wait, does it?

09:04.460 --> 09:05.878
- Ladies and gentlemen,

09:05.962 --> 09:08.339
welcome
to Junior Comedian's Night!

09:08.422 --> 09:10.591
Please give a hearty
Chortle Portal welcome

09:10.675 --> 09:14.220
to our first comedian,
Lincoln Loud!

09:14.303 --> 09:16.973
[cheers and applause]
- Lincoln?

09:17.056 --> 09:19.558
And what's he doing
with my joke notebooks?

09:19.642 --> 09:20.893
- [clears throat]

09:20.977 --> 09:22.812
Hello, Royal Woods.

09:22.895 --> 09:24.647
So, did you hear
that the lipstick

09:24.730 --> 09:26.857
and the eyeliner
got into a fight?

09:26.941 --> 09:28.776
Because seven ate nine!

09:28.859 --> 09:31.654
- [gasps]
That's the wrong punch line!

09:31.737 --> 09:35.116
- Never mind, here's one I know
you're gonna love.

09:35.199 --> 09:38.327
Why did the chickpea
cross the road?

09:38.411 --> 09:40.663
Wait, that doesn't make sense.

09:40.746 --> 09:42.081
Oh! Chicken!

09:42.164 --> 09:44.792
This writing is
really hard to read.

09:45.918 --> 09:48.296
Why did the students
eat their homework?

09:48.379 --> 09:51.924
Because their teacher said
it would be a piece of pie!

09:52.008 --> 09:53.676
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:53.759 --> 09:55.344
- No, no, no!

09:56.512 --> 09:58.180
The punch line is
"piece of cake"!

09:58.264 --> 10:01.851
[laughter]

10:01.934 --> 10:03.060
Oh. [chuckles]

10:03.144 --> 10:04.186
His delivery was
a little crummy.

10:04.270 --> 10:06.605
[laughter]

10:06.689 --> 10:09.775
But don't worry,
things are about to get batter.

10:09.859 --> 10:10.901
[laughter]

10:10.985 --> 10:12.361
Did you hear about the race

10:12.445 --> 10:13.863
between the lettuce
and the tomato?

10:13.946 --> 10:15.448
The lettuce was a head,

10:15.531 --> 10:17.533
but the tomato was
trying to ketchup!

10:17.616 --> 10:18.951
[laughter]

10:19.035 --> 10:20.703
Why couldn't Timmy
ride a bicycle?

10:20.786 --> 10:22.997
Because Timmy was a goldfish!

10:26.000 --> 10:27.376
- There she is!

10:27.460 --> 10:29.545
{\an1}The winner of
the Junior Comedian's Contest!

10:29.628 --> 10:32.548
- Oh, I owe it all to you guys.

10:32.631 --> 10:36.510
Lincoln, thanks for stinking on
purpose so I'd get up on stage.

10:36.594 --> 10:38.846
- Uh... yes.
On purpose.

10:38.929 --> 10:40.556
Of course.

10:40.639 --> 10:42.308
- We think you're really funny,

10:42.391 --> 10:43.392
and we're proud of you.

10:43.476 --> 10:44.602
We're sorry we said

10:44.685 --> 10:45.561
that harsh stuff about you.

10:45.644 --> 10:48.064
- Thanks. That means a lot.

10:48.147 --> 10:50.941
And I know I can be
a little bit much sometimes.

10:51.025 --> 10:52.693
I'll try to tone it down.

10:52.777 --> 10:54.153
{\an3}- Whoops!

10:54.236 --> 10:56.405
- Mm...

10:56.489 --> 10:57.448
- Go ahead, you can say it.

10:57.531 --> 11:00.534
- Your breakfast is toast!

11:00.618 --> 11:02.286
And that's no yoking matter.

11:02.370 --> 11:05.164
{\an1}If you scramble,
you can make another!

11:05.247 --> 11:06.665
- It's good to have you back.

11:06.749 --> 11:09.168
- Hey, why are you heading
for the egg-sit?

11:09.251 --> 11:11.629
I'm bacon you to come back!

11:11.712 --> 11:12.963
[laughs]

11:13.047 --> 11:14.840
I crack myself up.
[laughs]

11:16.842 --> 11:19.804
<i>[rock music]</i>

11:19.887 --> 11:25.017
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:26.060 --> 11:27.436
<i>[eyes tinkling]</i>

11:27.520 --> 11:29.563
- [gasps]
O-M-Gosh!

11:29.647 --> 11:31.065
What does that mean?

11:33.025 --> 11:36.821
- Okay, Leni should be
occupied for a while.

11:36.904 --> 11:39.740
I told her she can communicate
with Cliff by blinking.

11:39.824 --> 11:41.784
- I call this meeting to order!

11:41.867 --> 11:44.954
- We've tried throwing a few
surprise parties in this family,

11:45.037 --> 11:46.372
but it's always gone wrong.

11:46.455 --> 11:47.790
And we all know why.

11:47.873 --> 11:50.876
Or should I say, who.

11:50.960 --> 11:52.002
- Okay, she's coming.

11:52.086 --> 11:52.878
Everyone hide.

11:56.215 --> 11:57.091
- Leni, what are you doing?

11:57.174 --> 12:00.386
{\an1}- Shh! I'm hiding
for your surprise party.

12:00.469 --> 12:01.679
all: [groaning]

12:01.762 --> 12:03.305
- Siblings, I am perplexed

12:03.389 --> 12:04.807
{\an3}as to why have I just received
an invitation

12:04.890 --> 12:07.518
{\an3}to my own
surprise birthday party?

12:07.601 --> 12:08.978
- Oh! I sent that.

12:09.061 --> 12:10.354
I wanted to make sure
you'd be there.

12:10.438 --> 12:11.772
all: [groan]

12:11.856 --> 12:13.983
- Luna, should I wear
the pink or blue dress

12:14.066 --> 12:15.234
to your surprise party?

12:15.317 --> 12:16.735
- Dude.
- What?

12:16.819 --> 12:19.989
{\an1}- I pink you just blue
the surprise!

12:20.072 --> 12:21.782
{\an1}Ha, ha, ha!
Get it?

12:21.866 --> 12:23.742
But seriously, you ruined it.

12:23.826 --> 12:27.288
- Well, this year, we want to
throw a surprise party for Mom,

12:27.371 --> 12:29.331
which means,
as much as we love her,

12:29.415 --> 12:31.292
we have to keep Leni out of it.

12:31.375 --> 12:33.294
- Okay, guys.
Let me break it down for you.

12:33.377 --> 12:35.963
I'll do the cleaning.
Lola and Lynn are on food.

12:36.046 --> 12:37.715
Lana and Lucy will do
the decorations.

12:37.798 --> 12:39.508
Luan and Luna will handle
entertainment.

12:39.592 --> 12:41.343
Lisa will be in charge
of the guest list.

12:41.427 --> 12:43.596
And Dad will get Mom
out of the house.

12:43.679 --> 12:45.514
- What about me?
What's my job?

12:45.598 --> 12:48.100
- You have the most important
job of all.

12:48.184 --> 12:49.977
You have to keep Leni distracted
till Mom comes home.

12:50.060 --> 12:53.230
If she's coming our way,
just yell a code word.

12:53.314 --> 12:54.940
Let's make it daffodil.

12:55.024 --> 12:56.817
- Uh, can't it be
something cooler?

12:56.901 --> 12:59.570
Like serpent or quasar or--

12:59.653 --> 13:00.571
all: [scream]

13:00.654 --> 13:02.031
{\an3}- [screams]

13:02.114 --> 13:03.365
{\an3}Is this how
we're saying hello now?

13:03.449 --> 13:04.533
{\an3}I like it!
Don't mind me.

13:04.617 --> 13:05.826
Just getting my polish.

13:05.910 --> 13:06.368
{\an3}Cliff blinked
that he wants me

13:06.452 --> 13:08.287
to do his nails.

13:08.370 --> 13:09.914
Oh, by the way.

13:09.997 --> 13:11.999
{\an3}While I have you guys,
it's Mom's birthday today!

13:12.082 --> 13:13.709
{\an3}I was thinking
we should throw her

13:13.792 --> 13:15.920
{\an3}one of our famous
Loud family surprise parties.

13:16.003 --> 13:18.255
{\an3}If everyone agrees,
I'll go tell her right now!

13:18.339 --> 13:20.674
- Uh, actually, I don't think
Mom wants a party this year.

13:20.758 --> 13:23.052
Let's just keep it low-key.

13:23.135 --> 13:25.095
- Yeah, totes.
- Definitely.

13:25.179 --> 13:27.556
{\an3}- Uh, hey, Leni,
while you're here,

13:27.640 --> 13:30.559
{\an3}I have some urgent
fashion questions for you.

13:30.643 --> 13:34.230
{\an1}- Lincoln, all fashion questions
are urgent.

13:34.313 --> 13:36.524
- Okay, kids!
We're leaving now.

13:36.607 --> 13:40.945
I'm taking your mother shopping
because I love to shop!

13:41.028 --> 13:42.655
<i>[whoosh]</i>

13:42.738 --> 13:44.031
- We should stop including Dad

13:44.114 --> 13:46.909
{\an1}in the surprise party
planning too.

13:46.992 --> 13:48.744
- And this is plaid.

13:48.827 --> 13:52.498
{\an3}- So, um, is there a difference
between plaid and checkers?

13:52.581 --> 13:53.958
- Huge difference!

13:54.041 --> 13:55.459
{\an1}But to really help
you understand,

13:55.543 --> 13:58.754
{\an1}I should go get some samples
from downstairs.

13:58.837 --> 14:02.299
{\an3}- No! I mean, I have
a more important question.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.510
Is it ever okay to wear jorts?

14:04.593 --> 14:07.263
- O-M-Gosh, Lincoln!

14:07.346 --> 14:08.722
{\an1}We need to go back
to square one.

14:08.806 --> 14:11.267
- [sighs]
Ah!

14:11.350 --> 14:12.560
{\an3}- I need to hydrate
before we start.

14:12.643 --> 14:15.479
- Tulip! I mean daisy!

14:15.563 --> 14:17.147
The heck was that word?

14:17.231 --> 14:18.357
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:18.440 --> 14:19.984
- Ah!
<i>[alarm rings]</i>

14:21.193 --> 14:22.695
- Ooh, sorry, guys.

14:22.778 --> 14:24.029
Must've been something I ate.

14:26.407 --> 14:27.866
Hey, guys!
both: [scream]

14:27.950 --> 14:29.994
{\an1}- Oh, right.
I forgot our new greeting.

14:30.077 --> 14:32.204
{\an1}[screams]

14:35.165 --> 14:38.877
{\an1}Ooh, Lola, your cake chair
just gave me an idea.

14:38.961 --> 14:39.920
{\an1}Even if we're not
throwing Mom a party,

14:40.004 --> 14:41.755
{\an1}maybe we should make
her favorite cake.

14:41.839 --> 14:43.924
- You heard what Lori said.

14:44.008 --> 14:44.800
We're keeping it low-key.

14:44.883 --> 14:47.428
{\an1}- Daffodil!
[breathes heavily]

14:47.511 --> 14:51.140
- You're not ready
for floral prints, Lincoln.

14:51.223 --> 14:53.726
Well, that covers everything.

14:53.809 --> 14:54.977
- Literally.

14:55.060 --> 14:56.353
{\an1}- I'm gonna go gossip
with Cliff.

14:56.437 --> 14:57.396
{\an3}- Wait!

14:57.479 --> 15:01.567
{\an1}Uh, hey, you're always
looking for a dress model.

15:01.650 --> 15:02.484
Well, I'm your guy!

15:02.568 --> 15:05.070
{\an3}- [gasps]

15:05.154 --> 15:07.114
- My sisters owe me big time.
- What was that?

15:07.197 --> 15:12.036
{\an1}- Uh, I said, I think
we need to redo the hemline.

15:13.871 --> 15:14.496
- Keep it down, guys.

15:14.580 --> 15:17.416
Leni will hear.

15:17.499 --> 15:18.917
<i>[toes tinkling]</i>

15:19.001 --> 15:20.169
{\an3}- Ah! Oof!
[cymbal crashes]

15:20.252 --> 15:21.712
- What was that?
- Nothing.

15:21.795 --> 15:23.547
I didn't hear Luna
drop her cymbals.

15:23.631 --> 15:24.673
{\an3}I mean, uh--
[gasps]

15:24.757 --> 15:26.967
Daffodil! Daffodil!

15:27.051 --> 15:28.802
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:28.886 --> 15:31.055
Luna, you gotta--
oof--

15:31.138 --> 15:32.139
{\an1}[yelling]

15:32.222 --> 15:33.682
Oof! Oof! Oof!

15:33.766 --> 15:35.142
Daffodil...

15:37.519 --> 15:40.356
{\an3}- Lincoln, you need to get
your proverbial act together.

15:40.439 --> 15:42.191
{\an1}- Yeah,
we'll never get this done

15:42.274 --> 15:44.109
{\an1}if we have to keep
starting over.

15:44.193 --> 15:45.486
- Are you okay, Lincoln?

15:45.569 --> 15:47.154
If you want to jump down
the stairs,

15:47.237 --> 15:49.698
I have just the thing:
parachute pants!

15:49.782 --> 15:52.201
Oh, Lana, those popped balloons
on your hat

15:52.284 --> 15:52.951
just gave me an idea.

15:53.035 --> 15:54.787
I know we're not having a party,

15:54.870 --> 15:56.372
but shouldn't we at least do

15:56.455 --> 15:58.207
a little decorating
for Mom's birthday?

15:58.290 --> 16:01.210
- To repeat, keeping it low-key.

16:01.293 --> 16:03.253
- But you know
what we could use?

16:03.337 --> 16:04.296
A great card!

16:04.380 --> 16:05.923
Maybe one with a camel...

16:06.006 --> 16:09.051
in a space suit...
that's also scratch-and-sniff...

16:09.134 --> 16:10.469
and that says,

16:10.552 --> 16:12.680
"Happy birthday
from your 11 kids!"

16:12.763 --> 16:13.806
{\an1}- Adorbs!

16:13.889 --> 16:15.224
But where would I find one?

16:15.307 --> 16:17.393
- The Hazeltucky Party Outlet!

16:17.476 --> 16:20.062
- Hmm, that's, like,
three bus rides away.

16:20.145 --> 16:22.898
But it's for Mom,
and she's totes worth it.

16:22.981 --> 16:24.066
Bye!

16:24.149 --> 16:26.193
- Nice thinking, big brother!

16:26.276 --> 16:28.445
{\an1}- Can someone help me
with the streamers?

16:28.529 --> 16:30.280
all: [gasp]
- Ah.

16:30.364 --> 16:31.824
- I forgot my shoes!

16:31.907 --> 16:33.534
Oh, wait, no, I didn't.

16:33.617 --> 16:34.910
{\an3}Kay, bye!

16:34.993 --> 16:36.161
all: [exhale]

16:36.245 --> 16:38.080
{\an1}- Okay,
we lost some valuable time,

16:38.163 --> 16:39.289
but we can still do this.

16:39.373 --> 16:40.332
Everyone back to work!

16:40.416 --> 16:44.002
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:44.086 --> 16:45.212
- Dang it.
I'm out of balloons.

16:45.295 --> 16:50.759
Ooh! I know!
My emergency stash of ABC gum!

16:50.843 --> 16:52.261
[gum snaps]

16:53.804 --> 16:57.516
<i>[light music]</i>

16:57.599 --> 17:04.064
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:04.147 --> 17:05.523
- [screams]

17:06.108 --> 17:08.861
Still not hot enough.

17:12.698 --> 17:14.324
- [hyperventilating]

17:16.577 --> 17:19.121
Mm, still not sweet enough.

17:19.204 --> 17:21.749
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:21.832 --> 17:22.833
[doorbell rings]

17:22.915 --> 17:24.292
- The guests have arrived.

17:24.376 --> 17:26.462
{\an3}[lips smacking]
- How do!

17:26.545 --> 17:27.796
{\an3}Flip has a policy
of never showing up

17:27.880 --> 17:30.591
empty-handed, so here!

17:30.674 --> 17:31.717
- Expired milk?

17:31.800 --> 17:33.093
Gee, how thoughtful.

17:33.177 --> 17:34.678
{\an3}- You're welcome!
[burps]

17:34.762 --> 17:36.805
Uh, where's the grub?

17:36.889 --> 17:40.184
- Eh, someone turn on
the boob tube.

17:41.226 --> 17:43.312
Ooh! Color. Fancy.

17:43.395 --> 17:46.607
- Dr. Feinstein, greetings.

17:50.152 --> 17:51.904
{\an1}- How in the world
did you come up

17:51.987 --> 17:53.781
with this abysmal guest list?

17:53.864 --> 17:55.240
- According to my algorithm,

17:55.324 --> 17:57.576
{\an3}the people Mother encounters
most are:

17:57.659 --> 18:00.454
{\an3}her employer,
our cantankerous neighbor,

18:00.537 --> 18:02.915
{\an3}and the owner
of our local convenience store.

18:02.998 --> 18:04.917
{\an1}- Just because
she encounters them

18:05.000 --> 18:06.835
doesn't mean she likes them.

18:06.919 --> 18:09.421
- Well, just because
she uses toilet paper

18:09.505 --> 18:13.383
doesn't mean she'll find it
a suitable party decoration.

18:13.467 --> 18:14.968
{\an1}- Ugh, I told you
we should've just stuck

18:15.052 --> 18:16.637
with my brown balloons.

18:16.720 --> 18:18.889
{\an1}- Yeah, because everyone wants
their party to look

18:18.972 --> 18:20.599
like Cliff's litter box.

18:20.682 --> 18:23.101
- Hey, guys, I got
some great jokes for the party!

18:23.185 --> 18:25.521
[clears throat]
Boy, Mom is so old,

18:25.604 --> 18:27.815
her social security number is 1!

18:27.898 --> 18:30.984
I would have invited guests
from Mom's first birthday party,

18:31.068 --> 18:32.528
but they're all extinct.

18:32.611 --> 18:34.196
{\an3}- I don't think
Mom wants to hear jokes

18:34.279 --> 18:35.531
about how old she is.

18:35.614 --> 18:37.115
- Boss man's got a point, dude.

18:37.199 --> 18:37.866
{\an1}Why don't we just stick
to my jams

18:37.950 --> 18:39.993
for the entertainment?

18:40.077 --> 18:43.038
[screams indistinctly]

18:43.121 --> 18:44.790
♪ ♪

18:44.873 --> 18:45.958
[cord unplugs]

18:46.041 --> 18:48.961
- Um, Mom is going to hate that!

18:49.044 --> 18:51.046
It'll make her ears bleed!

18:51.129 --> 18:53.340
- Right after her teeth fall out
from eating your cake!

18:57.302 --> 19:00.013
- [screams]

19:00.097 --> 19:01.515
[gurgling]

19:01.598 --> 19:02.975
[spits]

19:03.058 --> 19:05.102
{\an1}- Lynn, what did you put
in that sub?

19:05.185 --> 19:07.479
{\an1}You're going to burn off
Mom's taste buds!

19:07.563 --> 19:11.316
{\an3}- Don't criticize my job
when you could barely do yours.

19:11.400 --> 19:13.402
[all shouting indistinctly]

19:13.485 --> 19:15.028
- [whistles]

19:15.112 --> 19:16.572
Guys, stop arguing!

19:16.655 --> 19:18.198
You're missing
the bigger picture.

19:18.282 --> 19:19.867
This party literally stinks.

19:19.950 --> 19:21.910
- You're right.
- Look at this mess.

19:21.994 --> 19:24.454
[indistinct muttering]

19:24.538 --> 19:26.748
{\an3}- I don't get it.
Where did we go wrong?

19:26.832 --> 19:28.041
We've never thrown
a bad party before.

19:28.125 --> 19:30.502
- Are we missing something?

19:30.586 --> 19:33.589
- Yeah, a decent sports package!

19:33.672 --> 19:35.215
- [gasps]
It's Leni!

19:35.299 --> 19:37.092
She may spoil all the surprises,

19:37.175 --> 19:40.512
but she's the only one who knows
how to throw a good party.

19:40.596 --> 19:42.014
- Lincoln's right.

19:42.097 --> 19:43.932
Leni actually thinks about
what people like.

19:44.016 --> 19:47.185
- We need to call her
and get her back here right now.

19:48.186 --> 19:50.939
[cell phone chirping]
- Ooh! A musical card.

19:51.023 --> 19:53.150
[chirping continues]

19:53.233 --> 19:55.569
Eh, I don't think
Mom would be into that.

19:55.652 --> 19:57.946
I like it, though.
I should make it my ringtone.

19:58.030 --> 19:58.906
- She's not answering.

19:58.989 --> 20:01.241
- We have to go get her.

20:01.325 --> 20:02.367
- [snoring]

20:03.201 --> 20:07.456
{\an3}- Sorry, gentlemen.
The soiree has concluded.

20:07.539 --> 20:09.291
- Hold up there, four-eyes!

20:09.374 --> 20:13.629
{\an1}Flip also has a policy of never
leaving a party empty-handed.

20:13.712 --> 20:15.672
Heh, heh, heh!
Okay, let's go.

20:15.756 --> 20:18.258
Come on, move it or lose it.

20:18.342 --> 20:18.967
- I guess we really blew it.

20:19.051 --> 20:20.302
We couldn't find Leni,

20:20.385 --> 20:22.679
{\an1}and now we can't
give Mom a decent--

20:22.763 --> 20:25.474
- Surprise!
<i>[cheesy brass music plays]</i>

20:25.557 --> 20:25.974
Oh, it's you guys.

20:26.058 --> 20:26.975
Hurry up and hide.

20:27.059 --> 20:29.311
Mom will be home any minute.

20:29.394 --> 20:31.313
- Leni, what's going on?

20:31.396 --> 20:32.481
- Don't be mad.

20:32.564 --> 20:33.482
I know you wanted to go low-key,

20:33.565 --> 20:35.442
but I found all this great stuff
at the store,

20:35.525 --> 20:39.029
and I decided
maybe we should go high-key.

20:39.112 --> 20:41.240
Doesn't Mom totally deserve it?

20:41.323 --> 20:43.325
Plus, I found that card
you wanted me to get.

20:43.408 --> 20:44.826
It is totes cute.

20:44.910 --> 20:48.163
And it's
a scratch-and-sniff too!

20:48.246 --> 20:50.707
- [sniffs]
Ugh. Camel!

20:50.791 --> 20:52.876
{\an3}- Give me that!
[sniffs]

20:52.960 --> 20:55.045
Ah! Camel...

20:55.128 --> 21:00.008
- I guess I'll put my key in
and open the front door now!

21:00.092 --> 21:01.551
- [gasps]
Mom's here!

21:01.635 --> 21:05.555
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:05.639 --> 21:07.057
all: Surprise!

21:07.140 --> 21:09.351
- [gasps]
Oh, my goodness!

21:09.434 --> 21:11.019
- Happy birthday, Mom!

21:11.103 --> 21:14.731
{\an3}- Oh, kids, you've really
outdone yourselves.

21:14.815 --> 21:16.692
Look at these decorations!

21:16.775 --> 21:19.945
{\an3}You remembered
violet is my favorite color.

21:20.028 --> 21:21.822
And do I smell pad thai?

21:21.905 --> 21:24.324
{\an3}- Yep, and German chocolate
cake for dessert.

21:24.408 --> 21:26.326
- Thank you so much, kids.

21:26.410 --> 21:28.495
This is the perfect party.

21:28.578 --> 21:30.539
- Actually,
you should thank Leni.

21:30.622 --> 21:32.165
We tried to do this without her,

21:32.249 --> 21:33.959
but it was a disaster.

21:34.042 --> 21:36.920
- What do you mean,
you tried to do it without me?

21:37.004 --> 21:38.213
- Uh, yeah.

21:38.296 --> 21:39.673
We're sorry, Leni.

21:39.756 --> 21:41.883
We were afraid
you'd spoil the surprise.

21:41.967 --> 21:44.219
We didn't realize
you're the only one of us

21:44.302 --> 21:46.930
thoughtful enough to make
a party really special.

21:47.014 --> 21:48.598
- In fact, from now on,

21:48.682 --> 21:51.935
how would you like to be
our official party planner?

21:52.019 --> 21:54.563
- Yay! Thanks, you guys.

21:54.646 --> 21:55.897
You hear that, Dad?

21:55.981 --> 21:57.399
{\an1}I'm planning
your surprise party next.

21:57.482 --> 21:59.568
{\an1}But don't worry,
I'll send an invitation.

22:02.696 --> 22:03.572
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:03.655 --> 22:06.283
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:06.366 --> 22:08.368
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:08.452 --> 22:11.288
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:11.371 --> 22:15.250
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:15.333 --> 22:16.835
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.918 --> 22:18.545
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:18.628 --> 22:19.921
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:20.005 --> 22:21.256
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee ♪</i>

22:21.339 --> 22:22.507
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:22.591 --> 22:24.593
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:24.676 --> 22:26.053
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:26.136 --> 22:28.680
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
